x4freetext: Self-supporting metal foils of 99.5% enriched 66-Zn
(thickness 2.5 mg/cm2), were irradiated with 16-O
beam.
A short (5 min) and a long (60 min) irradiation
were carried out at each of the beam energies.
The recoiling products were collected on
aluminium catcher foils of thickness 2 mg/cm2.

A short (5 min) and a long (60 min) irradiation
were carried out at each of the beam energies.

Self-supporting metal foils of 99.5% enriched 66-Zn
(thickness 2.5 mg/cm2), were irradiated with 16-O
beam.
-By authors.  The cross-sections of the two 78-Rb
isomers, 78-Rb-M (jpi=4-) and 78-Rb-G (jpi=0+) were
deduced by fitting the common gamma-line of 455 keV
into two independently decaying radionuclides. The 10%
it-decay of 78-Rb-M to 78-Rb-G was neglected.

(thickness 2.5 mg/cm2), were irradiated with 16-O
beam.
A short (5 min) and a long (60 min) irradiation
were carried out at each of the beam energies.
The recoiling products were collected on

-By authors.  In the case of 77-Br, the high-spin
isomer 77-Br-M decays by isomer transition (100%) to
ground state 77-Br-G and hence the cross-section of
77-Br-G represents the sum of the cross-sections of
both the isomers.
